<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-167-422  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 167 422.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  April 3 1989 v35 n1752 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bills would allow joint output, marketing. (introduced into the101st Congress)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Barrett, Joyce.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Legislation has been introduced into the 101st Congress, designedto increase US competitiveness by amending antitrust laws topermit American firms to enter into joint-production and marketingventures.andP;  The bills are in response to foreign competition thatindustry sources say is pressuring US electronics and computerfirms out of the high-technology fields.andP;  The issue of looseningantitrust restrictions has such widespread industry andCongressional support, that some change is expected in theantitrust law in 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     LegislationCompetitionAntitrust LawsJoint VentureMarketing AgreementsProduct DevelopmentComputer industryForeign Competition.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>